r, but never really pray without surrender. You can fight without ever winning, but never ever win without a fight.\n\n- Neil\n|\nGod’s word is not just to be heard and repeated, it is to be breathed, lived, and emulated with each action.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nIf a person is not talented enough to be a novelist, not smart enough to be a lawyer, and his hands are too shaky to perform operations, he becomes a journalist.\n\n- Norman\n|\nIf you are not serving the Lord, start serving Him, so that you will be a partaker of His blessings\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThe Lord works through deeply flawed people, since He made so few of the other kind.\n\n- Timothy B. Tyson, Blood Done Sign My Name: A True Story\n|\nWith the plundered people transferring their energies into relaxed and receptive thoughts, degradation and lust for power produced art.\n\n- Peter Weiss, The Aesthetics of Resistance, Vol. 1\n|\nWhen I reached 70, the doc said I should try walking 5 miles a day. At 72, I'm still trying to find my way home ☺️\n\n- Jacqueline\n|\nCommerce does not have to be a ruthless, brutal enterprise that damages people’s lives. It can be a source of happiness, healing, and hope.\n\n- Brian de Haaff, Lovability: How to Build a Business That People Love and Be Happy Doing It\n|\nIs this thing safe?''Safe as life,' Gansey replied.\n\n- Maggie Stiefvater, The Raven Boys\n|\nOur thoughts and perceptions are our god.Our true inner awareness is the purest temple,where I worship every day for the divine.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWe, ignorant of ourselves,Beg often our own harms, which the wise powersDeny us for our good; so find we profitBy losing of our prayers.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Antony and Cleopatra\n|\nWhenever you make up your mind to go into solitude, you must decide first of all what you want to go and do there.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nWhen has life listened to anyone?It goes on at its own pace...Limping, when we wish it should run,And when calm desired, sprinting as in a race…\n\n- Neelam\n|\nMy task is set before me, girl My mission clear and true There’ll be black knights and dragons, girl But I will always come for you…\n\n- Emme\n|\nWhen I was earning, saving, and spending, I felt poor. When I started to give away some of my earning for good purposes, abundance filled my heart.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you dont know learn how to be scared, you'll never really learn how to be brave.\n\n- Simon Holt, The Devouring\n|\nActing courageously is about knowing and making the right choices based on a deep conviction that dwarfs fear, doubt, and worry.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nHe was discovering that even hatred died a little at the end. But it still lasted longer than desire, longer even than love.\n\n- P.D.\n|\nBeauty and Money will get you a relationship , but not love. Listening, caring and being there will get you Love.\n\n- De\n|\nMissing a train is only painful if you run after it! Likewise, not matching the idea of success others expect from you is only painful if that’s what you are seeking.\n\n- Nassim Nicholas Taleb, The Black Swan: The Impact of the Highly Improbable\n|\nA single day is enough to make us a little larger or, another time, a little smaller.\n\n- Paul\n|\nEven as a child, even as my blood-past was drained from me, I understood that if I were strong enough to accept it, I was being offered a second history.\n\n- Anne\n|\nPiglet sidled up to Pooh from behind. 'Pooh!' he whispered.'Yes, Piglet?''Nothing,' said Piglet, taking Pooh's paw. 'I just wanted to be sure of you.\n\n- A.A. Milne, The House at Pooh Corner\n|\nIf you stop tending to flowers when they lose a few petals, you will never grow a garden.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nIf we stretch ourselves to open our minds, to see our shared humanity with others, we allow ourselves to see the existence of community and generosity in unexpected places.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg,